You are implementing the Stage 9 Render + Stitch panel (`components/stages/Stage9RenderStitch.tsx`) for a video production pipeline editor. This client component manages parallel Remotion section rendering and ffmpeg full-video stitching with real-time progress tracking.

Requirements
1. Props: `onAdvance: () => void`.
2. Section render table: columns section ID, duration (seconds), status badge, progress bar (0–100%), [▶] modal preview, [↺] re-render.
3. Active renders panel: shows up to 3 simultaneous progress bars (each labeled with section ID).
4. [Render ▾] dropdown: options All / Missing / Selected. Triggers `POST /api/pipeline/render/run` with appropriate `{ sections }`.
5. [Stitch Full Video] button: triggers `POST /api/pipeline/stitch/run`. Disabled while renders are in progress.
6. Full Video panel: shows file size, duration, [Open in Review →] button that switches to Review tab.
7. All progress bars update via SSE stream for the active render job.
8. `'use client'` directive.

Dependencies

